category: STATE CAPITALS OF INDIA
category comment: 

clue: The most populous city in India, this capital of Maharashtra state is also home to the country's leading stock exchange

response: Mumbai

clue: Formerly Calcutta, Kolkata is capital of "West" this state; the "East" part became its own country in 1971

response: Bengal

clue: You've probably talked to a call center in Karnataka's capital, this city known as the "Silicon Valley of India"

response: Bangalore

clue: This capital of Madhya Pradesh state is known as the City of Lakes, but sadly also as the site of a Union Carbide disaster

response: Bhopal

clue: Panaji is the capital of this 3-letter state, one of India's smallest & a possession of Portugal for more than 4 centuries

response: Goa

